headlines.description: — Keon Johnson led a balanced Brooklyn attack with 18 points, and the Nets snapped a seven-game losing streak with a 104-83 win over the Charlotte Hornets on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Keon Johnson scores 18 points as Nets beat Hornets 104-83 to snap 7-game losing streak

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam scored 37 points, Tyrese Haliburton had 30 points and eight assists, and the Indiana Pacers beat the Detroit Pistons 133-119 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam scores 37, Haliburton adds 30 points and 8 assists to lead Pacers past Pistons 133-119

headlines.description: — Scottie Barnes scored 24 points and the Toronto Raptors beat NBA-worst Washington 106-82 on Wednesday night for their fifth straight victory and the Wizards' 15th loss in a row.
headlines.shortLinkText: Raptors rout the NBA-worst Wizards 106-82 for their 5th straight victory

headlines.description: — Kristaps Porzingis scored 26 of his season-high 34 points in the first half, and the Boston Celtics coasted to a 122-100 victory over the Chicago Bulls on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kristaps Porzingis finishes with 34 points, carrying Celtics over Bulls 122-100

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 34 points, Ty Jerome added 20 off the bench and the Cleveland Cavaliers never trailed in a 126-106 win over the Miami Heat on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Donovan Mitchell scores 34 points, Cavaliers never trail in 126-106 win over Heat

events.name: Denver Nuggets at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson had 30 points and 15 assists, OG Anunoby scored 23 points and the New York Knicks beat the Denver Nuggets 122-112 on Wednesday night for their fifth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson has 30 points and 15 assists as Knicks beat slumping Nuggets 122-112 for 5th straight win

headlines.description: — Tyrese Maxey scored 30 points to lead the Philadelphia 76ers past the Sacramento Kings 117-104 on Wednesday night for their fourth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Maxey scores 30 points and 76ers top Kings 117-104 for their 4th straight victory

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — P.J. Washington scored 25 points, making all four of his 3-point attempts in the fourth quarter, and Kyrie Irving added 25 points and six assists as the Dallas Mavericks outlasted the New Orleans Pelicans 137-136 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Washington leads the Mavericks to a 137-136 victory over the Pelicans

events.name: LA Clippers at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard and Norman Powell had 27 points each and the Los Angeles Clippers rallied to beat the San Antonio Spurs 128-116 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Leonard, Powell fuel 4th-quarter push as Clippers beat Wembanyama, Spurs, 128-116

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 33 points, Julius Randle added 28 and the Minnesota Timberwolves beat the Phoenix Suns 121-113 on Wednesday night for their fourth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Edwards scores 33 points as Timberwolves beat Suns 121-113 for 4th straight win

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry hit a long 3-pointer with 1:52 left on the way to 21 points, Andrew Wiggins scored 27 and the Golden State Warriors beat the Western Conference-leading Oklahoma City Thunder 116-109 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 52 but Curry and Wiggins lead balanced Warriors past Thunder 116-109
